{{distinguish|mixed raster content}} {{Infobox file format | name = mrc | extension = <tt>.mrc</tt> | mime = | owner = | genre = 3D [[electron density]] file or 2D image file | url = http://www.ccpem.ac.uk/mrc_format/mrc2014.php }}
'''MRC''' is a file format that has become industry standard in [[cryo-electron microscopy]] (cryoEM) and [[electron tomography]] (ET), where the result of the technique is a three-dimensional grid of [[voxel]]s each with a value corresponding to [[electron density]] or [[electric potential]]. It was developed by the MRC ([[Medical Research Council (United Kingdom)|Medical Research Council, UK]]) Laboratory of Molecular Biology.<ref name="MRCImage"/> In 2014, the format was standardised.<ref name="MRC2014"/> The format specification is available on the [http://www.ccpem.ac.uk/mrc_format/mrc2014.php CCP-EM website].
The MRC format is supported by many of the software packages listed in [[b:Software Tools For Molecular Microscopy]].
==See also== *[[CCP4 (file format)]]
